<span>
The span element is a generic text container. It does not create a new line like the p element does. 
This element is invisible by default but can be used for styling words or phrases within a larger body of text.

<div>
The div element is a generic container. It is used primarily for grouping other HTML elements together. 
It is invisible by default but can be used to position or style a group of elements.


